The 14th edition of the Lagos Advertising and Ideas Festival (LAIF) Awards, organised by the Association of Advertising Agencies of Nigeria (AAAN) will hold tomorrow in Lagos. A statement signed by the AAAN Publicity Secretary, Jenkins Alumona, mentioned the theme for this year’s awards ceremony as ‘Tori Tori of LAIF.’ Alumona said that the grand finale of the LAIF Awards, an international status affair that debuted in 2006 with the aim of recognising, rewarding and fostering creative excellence in all areas of marketing communications, would be a glamorous event that would attract industry captains, business leaders and policy makers, as well as local and international brand luminaries. Honourees at this year’s awards ceremony are the former Managing Director of Eminent Communications Limited, the late Mr Sesan Ogunro, and the Chairman, LTC/JWT, Mr Billy Lawson. AAAN’s rescheduled 46th AGM to hold in Lagos DDB Lagos, Insight Publicis win big at 2018 LAIF awards AAAN holds cocktail for women in advertising